question: Good choice. We’re getting right to the heart of life's most essential questions. Let’s get started. Do you have a focus in your life?
Hmmm. Let me ask you another question: Do you think it is important to follow other people’s visions?
Here's why. No one should waste their time living someone else’s life. Don’t be trapped inside other people’s thinking. Remember, Your time is limited. Let's move on with another question
How much time do you dedicate to things that you feel are personally important for you? Click a choice
Here’s why: My favorite things in life don’t cost any money at all. It’s really clear that the most precious resource we all have is time. Let's go on
Here’s a completely different question. It’s personal. Ready? What would you do if this were the last day of your life? Pick a button.

As a working adult, I looked in the mirror every morning and asked myself, ‘If today were the last day of my life, would I want to do what I am about to do today?’ And whenever the answer was ‘No’, I knew I needed to change something. We don’t get to do that many things. Every one should be really excellent. Because this is our life.
Let’s continue and get really personal. Are you, personally, afraid of death? Pick a button.

Why do I say that? Here’s why. Remembering that I would be dead soon was the most important tool I ever encountered to help me make the big choices in life. Everything: all external expectations, all pride, all fear of embarrassment or failure, these things just fall away in the face of death, leaving only what is truly important.
Congratulations, This is the last question of this “Meaning of Life and Death” Topic. I’m going to make it very simple. What’s the most productive and creative approach to life? Pick one.

Your EQ Rating is a measure of your emotional attitude toward your life and work. And that wraps up this session. In future sessions, we will tune your emotional attitude to optimize your success in life.

Last thing I want to show you is how your emotional attitude is broken down into these components: leadership, innovation, stability, and empathy. In future sessions, we will train you like an athlete, to obtain maximum success in your life. This is what being a Life Coach is all about. That's it for now. Great getting started on the road to success. See you next session.
